University ERP

PROJECT OVERVIEW The University ERP (Enterprise Resource Planning)
System is a comprehensive, cross-platform desktop application developed to manage and streamline the core administrative,
academic, and student-related functions of an educational institution. This project is built using the Java programming
language and leverages the Swing GUI framework with a modern look and feel provided by FlatLaf. The system provides distinct,
role-based modules for Administrators, Faculty, and Students, ensuring a centralized and efficient platform for all academic operations.

KEY FEATURES BY USER ROLE The system is designed with a multi-role structure, providing customized functionality for each type of user:

ADMINISTRATOR MODULE
User Management: The Administrator can add and manage details for Students and Faculty.
Course & Section Management: They can view the complete course catalog and create new course sections.
System Settings: The Administrator can set the active registration deadline for students.

FACULTY (INSTRUCTOR) MODULE

Section Management: Instructors can view a list of all course sections currently assigned to them.
Student Roster & Grading: They can access the list of students enrolled in each section and manage their grades.
Assessment Creation: Instructors have the functionality to create and remove assessments (components) for their courses.
Performance Analysis: The module includes tools for visualizing component-wise performance graphs for the class.

STUDENT MODULE

Course Registration: Students can view available courses and register for sections during the active registration period.
Academic History & Grades: They can view all registered courses and their associated grades.
Performance View: Students can check their component-wise scores for individual subjects.
CGPA Calculation: The system provides functionality to calculate and display the student's current and semester-wise CGPA.


TECHNOLOGY STACK The application employs a robust architecture utilizing several industry-standard technologies and libraries:
Core Language and Framework: Java and the Swing GUI framework.
Database: H2 Database for data storage and persistence.



SETUP AND INSTALLATION Prerequisites: Ensure that you have a compatible Java Development Kit (JDK 8 or newer) installed on your system. Running the Application: The project is packaged for easy execution:

Source Retrieval: Clone the project repository (harshita24251/ap_project).


